{
  "title": "Database",
  "description": "Low-level key/value database abstraction used by CacheStore implementations. Data is organised into named object stores (`type`) that act as namespaces, each holding entries keyed by `name`. IndexedDbDatabase is the built-in implementation; custom backends can be provided by implementing this interface and wrapping it in a CacheStore.",
